<paragraph blockId="6.[213,1170,1537,1720]" pageId="6" pageNumber="2219">
<emphasis box="[213,278,1537,1561]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="2219">Male.</emphasis>
Length of forewings 
<quantity box="[521,683,1537,1561]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.915" metricValueMax="4.96" metricValueMin="4.87" pageId="6" pageNumber="2219" unit="mm" value="4.915" valueMax="4.96" valueMin="4.87">4.87–4.96 mm</quantity>
. Colouration of head and thorax light reddish brown, setal warts and abdomen stramineous. Forewing light reddish brown, with an oval, pale macula parallel to the costal margin (pterostigma), a circular dark spot over nigma, and dark stripes over transversal veins. General colouration of wing paler and less contrasting than that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Martynov" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[584,701,1665,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Smicridea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="2219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruana">
<emphasis box="[584,701,1665,1689]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="2219">S. peruana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[716,832,1664,1688]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="14.[213,280,1502,1524]" captionTargetBox="[215,1170,160,1469]" captionTargetId="figure-5@14.[213,1170,160,1469]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 5. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) pampeana. (A) Male genitalia, lateral view; (B) male genitalia, dorsal view; (C) inferior appendages, ventral view; (D) phallus, lateral view; (E) phallus, ventral view. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) peruana. (F) colouration pattern of forewing, (G) male genitalia, lateral view; (H) male genitalia, dorsal view; (I) inferior appendages, ventral view; (J) phallus, lateral view; (K) phallus, dorsal view (L) phallus, lateral view, with endophallus evaginated." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204297/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="2219">Figure 5F</figureCitation>
). The colouration of the body and wings was observed in specimens preserved in alcohol.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204291" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5204291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204291/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220" startId="7.[144,211,1356,1378]" targetBox="[144,1101,162,1322]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[144,1101,1356,1465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220">
Figure 2. 
<taxonomicName authority="Rueda Martín &amp; Sganga, 2011" authorityName="Rueda Martín &amp; Sganga" authorityYear="2011" box="[247,633,1356,1378]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Smicridea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thermophila" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Rhyacophylax">
<emphasis box="[247,347,1356,1378]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220">Smicridea</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[360,501,1356,1378]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220">Rhyacophylax</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[514,633,1356,1378]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220">thermophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[638,716,1356,1377]" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, adult male. (A) Male genitalia, lateral view; (B) male genitalia, dorsal view; (C) phallus, dorsal detail of tip; (D) phallus, ventral detail of tip. 
<taxonomicName authority="Rueda Martín &amp; Sganga, 2011" authorityName="Rueda Martín &amp; Sganga" authorityYear="2011" box="[210,598,1414,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Smicridea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thermophila" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Rhyacophylax">
<emphasis box="[210,310,1414,1436]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220">Smicridea</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[324,465,1414,1436]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220">Rhyacophylax</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[479,598,1414,1436]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220">thermophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[604,682,1415,1436]" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, larva. (E) habitus; (F) head, dorsal view; (G) thoraxic nota; (H) anterior leg.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[144,1101,1531,1587]" box="[187,1101,1531,1556]" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220">Diameter of eye, in dorsal view, almost half of the interocular distance.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[144,1101,1531,1587]" box="[144,928,1563,1587]" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220">Anterolateral process of sternum V about 1.5 times length of sternum.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[144,1101,1632,1688]" lastBlockId="8.[213,1170,1377,1688]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="2221" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220">
<emphasis box="[144,253,1633,1657]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Segment IX with anterolateral margin rounded (
<figureCitation box="[828,952,1632,1656]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[144,211,1356,1378]" captionTargetBox="[144,1101,162,1322]" captionTargetId="figure-7@7.[144,1101,160,1323]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., adult male. (A) Male genitalia, lateral view; (B) male genitalia, dorsal view; (C) phallus, dorsal detail of tip; (D) phallus, ventral detail of tip. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., larva. (E) habitus; (F) head, dorsal view; (G) thoraxic nota; (H) anterior leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204291/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="2220">Figure 2A</figureCitation>
). Tergum X, in dorsal view, deeply divided mesally, internal margin of each hemitergite concave, posterior margin rounded (
<figureCitation box="[520,637,1377,1401]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[144,211,1356,1378]" captionTargetBox="[144,1101,162,1322]" captionTargetId="figure-7@7.[144,1101,160,1323]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., adult male. (A) Male genitalia, lateral view; (B) male genitalia, dorsal view; (C) phallus, dorsal detail of tip; (D) phallus, ventral detail of tip. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., larva. (E) habitus; (F) head, dorsal view; (G) thoraxic nota; (H) anterior leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204291/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="2221">Figure 2B</figureCitation>
); in lateral aspect with ventral margin rounded and tip lightly upturned (
<figureCitation box="[516,641,1409,1433]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[144,211,1356,1378]" captionTargetBox="[144,1101,162,1322]" captionTargetId="figure-7@7.[144,1101,160,1323]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., adult male. (A) Male genitalia, lateral view; (B) male genitalia, dorsal view; (C) phallus, dorsal detail of tip; (D) phallus, ventral detail of tip. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., larva. (E) habitus; (F) head, dorsal view; (G) thoraxic nota; (H) anterior leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204291/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="2221">Figure 2A</figureCitation>
). Inferior appendages two-segmented, setose; basal portion long and slender (two times longer than the apical segment), slightly inflated apicad; apical segment short, ending in a blunt point (
<figureCitation box="[920,1066,1473,1497]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[144,211,1356,1378]" captionTargetBox="[144,1101,162,1322]" captionTargetId="figure-7@7.[144,1101,160,1323]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., adult male. (A) Male genitalia, lateral view; (B) male genitalia, dorsal view; (C) phallus, dorsal detail of tip; (D) phallus, ventral detail of tip. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., larva. (E) habitus; (F) head, dorsal view; (G) thoraxic nota; (H) anterior leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204291/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="2221">Figure 2A,B</figureCitation>
). Phallus long, tubular, wide basally, with basal and apical sections meeting at an angle of about 100 
<superScript attach="left" box="[328,337,1533,1550]" fontSize="7" pageId="8" pageNumber="2221">◦</superScript>
(
<figureCitation box="[357,479,1537,1561]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[144,211,1356,1378]" captionTargetBox="[144,1101,162,1322]" captionTargetId="figure-7@7.[144,1101,160,1323]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., adult male. (A) Male genitalia, lateral view; (B) male genitalia, dorsal view; (C) phallus, dorsal detail of tip; (D) phallus, ventral detail of tip. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., larva. (E) habitus; (F) head, dorsal view; (G) thoraxic nota; (H) anterior leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204291/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="2221">Figure 2A</figureCitation>
); apical section lightly sinuous in lateral view, ending in an apicodorsal, mesal, retrorse point; tip of phallus with two lateral, sclerotized, thick spines, directed anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[527,677,1601,1625]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[144,211,1356,1378]" captionTargetBox="[144,1101,162,1322]" captionTargetId="figure-7@7.[144,1101,160,1323]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., adult male. (A) Male genitalia, lateral view; (B) male genitalia, dorsal view; (C) phallus, dorsal detail of tip; (D) phallus, ventral detail of tip. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., larva. (E) habitus; (F) head, dorsal view; (G) thoraxic nota; (H) anterior leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204291/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="2221">Figure 2C,D</figureCitation>
); internal sclerite simple, sinuate in lateral view, apex enlarged, forming an hexagonal plate in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[926,1043,1632,1656]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[144,211,1356,1378]" captionTargetBox="[144,1101,162,1322]" captionTargetId="figure-7@7.[144,1101,160,1323]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., adult male. (A) Male genitalia, lateral view; (B) male genitalia, dorsal view; (C) phallus, dorsal detail of tip; (D) phallus, ventral detail of tip. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., larva. (E) habitus; (F) head, dorsal view; (G) thoraxic nota; (H) anterior leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204291/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="2221">Figure 2C</figureCitation>
); in ventral view, endophallus with two lateral hook-like structures (
<figureCitation box="[841,962,1664,1688]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[144,211,1356,1378]" captionTargetBox="[144,1101,162,1322]" captionTargetId="figure-7@7.[144,1101,160,1323]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., adult male. (A) Male genitalia, lateral view; (B) male genitalia, dorsal view; (C) phallus, dorsal detail of tip; (D) phallus, ventral detail of tip. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., larva. (E) habitus; (F) head, dorsal view; (G) thoraxic nota; (H) anterior leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204291/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="2221">Figure 2D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204293" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5204293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204293/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="2221" startId="8.[213,280,1254,1276]" targetBox="[213,1167,161,1221]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph blockId="8.[213,1169,1254,1306]" pageId="8" pageNumber="2221">
Figure 3. 
<taxonomicName authority="Rueda Martín &amp; Sganga, 2011" authorityName="Rueda Martín &amp; Sganga" authorityYear="2011" box="[318,708,1254,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Smicridea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="2221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thermophila" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Rhyacophylax">
<emphasis box="[318,418,1255,1277]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="2221">Smicridea</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[433,574,1255,1277]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="2221">Rhyacophylax</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[589,708,1255,1277]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="2221">thermophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[715,795,1255,1276]" pageId="8" pageNumber="2221" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, pupa. (A) Labrum, dorsal view; (B) left mandible; (C) terminal abdominal segment, dorsal view; (D) abdominal dorsal plates.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[144,359,166,190]" box="[144,359,166,190]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">
<emphasis box="[144,230,166,190]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[144,1101,230,828]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">
<emphasis box="[144,217,231,254]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Larva.</emphasis>
Length: 
<quantity box="[322,408,230,254]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.2" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222" unit="mm" value="7.2">7.2 mm</quantity>
(
<emphasis box="[426,439,231,254]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">n</emphasis>
= 10) (
<figureCitation box="[530,650,230,254]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[144,211,1356,1378]" captionTargetBox="[144,1101,162,1322]" captionTargetId="figure-7@7.[144,1101,160,1323]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., adult male. (A) Male genitalia, lateral view; (B) male genitalia, dorsal view; (C) phallus, dorsal detail of tip; (D) phallus, ventral detail of tip. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., larva. (E) habitus; (F) head, dorsal view; (G) thoraxic nota; (H) anterior leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204291/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Figure 2E</figureCitation>
). Colouration of the head light reddish brown, with anterior margin of frontoclypeal apotome darker; pale (yellowish), oval maculae around stemmata, extending lateroposteriorly through parietal apotomes, joining to a transverse band at posterior end of head; yellowish at clypeus; with two lateral, dark reddish brown, oblique stripes over medial depression; and three pale maculae (two behind each anterior tentorial pit, and other at posterior end of frontoclypeal apotome); between the maculae there are six small, pale muscle scars (three at each side of the apotome), aligned obliquely as shown in 
<figureCitation box="[784,899,453,477]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[144,211,1356,1378]" captionTargetBox="[144,1101,162,1322]" captionTargetId="figure-7@7.[144,1101,160,1323]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., adult male. (A) Male genitalia, lateral view; (B) male genitalia, dorsal view; (C) phallus, dorsal detail of tip; (D) phallus, ventral detail of tip. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., larva. (E) habitus; (F) head, dorsal view; (G) thoraxic nota; (H) anterior leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204291/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">
Figure 
<specimenCount box="[865,899,453,477]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222" type="generic">2F</specimenCount>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[144,1101,230,828]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">
Head capsule quadrangular in dorsal view. Anterior margin of frontoclypeal apotome symmetrical, rounded, smooth at middle, with three dots at each side; lateral notches wide, lightly insinuated; medial U-shaped depression very marked (
<figureCitation box="[152,270,580,604]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[144,211,1356,1378]" captionTargetBox="[144,1101,162,1322]" captionTargetId="figure-7@7.[144,1101,160,1323]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., adult male. (A) Male genitalia, lateral view; (B) male genitalia, dorsal view; (C) phallus, dorsal detail of tip; (D) phallus, ventral detail of tip. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., larva. (E) habitus; (F) head, dorsal view; (G) thoraxic nota; (H) anterior leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204291/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Figure 2F</figureCitation>
). Postero-ventral apotome lacking. Labrum with a row of marginal setae. Chaetotaxy of the head typical of the genus. Parietal apotome with pale muscle scars, and anterolaterally bearing short pale setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[144,1101,230,828]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">
Nota and legs stramineous. Distribution of muscle scars on pro-, meso- and metanota as in 
<figureCitation box="[320,440,708,732]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[144,211,1356,1378]" captionTargetBox="[144,1101,162,1322]" captionTargetId="figure-7@7.[144,1101,160,1323]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., adult male. (A) Male genitalia, lateral view; (B) male genitalia, dorsal view; (C) phallus, dorsal detail of tip; (D) phallus, ventral detail of tip. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., larva. (E) habitus; (F) head, dorsal view; (G) thoraxic nota; (H) anterior leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204291/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Figure 2G</figureCitation>
. Poststernal sclerites of prosternum lacking. Mesosternum with two posterolateral subtriangular sclerites. Abdominal sternum VIII with two triangular sclerites bearing setae. Anterior leg with dark trocantin bearing three strong setae, tibia without pinnate setae, general chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[801,920,804,828]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[144,211,1356,1378]" captionTargetBox="[144,1101,162,1322]" captionTargetId="figure-7@7.[144,1101,160,1323]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., adult male. (A) Male genitalia, lateral view; (B) male genitalia, dorsal view; (C) phallus, dorsal detail of tip; (D) phallus, ventral detail of tip. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., larva. (E) habitus; (F) head, dorsal view; (G) thoraxic nota; (H) anterior leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204291/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Figure 2H</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[144,1101,867,1083]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">
<emphasis box="[144,210,868,891]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Pupa.</emphasis>
Length: 
<quantity box="[314,404,867,891]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
. Anterior margin of labrum rounded, with a shallow median depression, bearing short setae in the anterior margin; lateral lobes with setae longer than that of anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[468,586,931,955]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="8.[213,280,1254,1276]" captionTargetBox="[213,1167,161,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-5@8.[213,1170,161,1221]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 3. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., pupa. (A) Labrum, dorsal view; (B) left mandible; (C) terminal abdominal segment, dorsal view; (D) abdominal dorsal plates." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204293/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Figure 3A</figureCitation>
). Mandibles long, with inner margin finely serrated distally, and with long posterolateral setae; right mandible with three teeth, and left with four (
<figureCitation box="[306,423,995,1019]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="8.[213,280,1254,1276]" captionTargetBox="[213,1167,161,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-5@8.[213,1170,161,1221]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 3. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., pupa. (A) Labrum, dorsal view; (B) left mandible; (C) terminal abdominal segment, dorsal view; (D) abdominal dorsal plates." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204293/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Figure 3B</figureCitation>
). Abdominal terga with pairs of anterior plates on segments II to VIII and posterior plates on segment III and IV (
<figureCitation box="[750,870,1027,1051]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="8.[213,280,1254,1276]" captionTargetBox="[213,1167,161,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-5@8.[213,1170,161,1221]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 3. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., pupa. (A) Labrum, dorsal view; (B) left mandible; (C) terminal abdominal segment, dorsal view; (D) abdominal dorsal plates." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204293/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Figure 3D</figureCitation>
). Apical appendages long and bearing long straight setae (
<figureCitation box="[561,679,1059,1083]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="8.[213,280,1254,1276]" captionTargetBox="[213,1167,161,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-5@8.[213,1170,161,1221]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 3. Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) thermophila sp. nov., pupa. (A) Labrum, dorsal view; (B) left mandible; (C) terminal abdominal segment, dorsal view; (D) abdominal dorsal plates." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5204293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5204293/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Figure 3C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[144,428,1147,1171]" box="[144,428,1147,1171]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">
<emphasis box="[144,428,1147,1171]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Systematic considerations</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[144,1101,1186,1274]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">The male genitalia of this new species is like no other described species in the genus. The tip of the phallus with the apicodorsal, retrorse point and the lateral spines is unique.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[144,264,1338,1362]" box="[144,264,1338,1362]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">
<emphasis box="[144,264,1338,1362]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[144,1100,1377,1433]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">
From the Greek words 
<emphasis box="[438,526,1378,1402]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">thermos</emphasis>
for hot and 
<emphasis box="[699,763,1378,1402]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">philos</emphasis>
for friend, referring to the temperature of the water where the larvae were found.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[144,229,1497,1521]" box="[144,229,1497,1521]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">
<emphasis box="[144,229,1497,1521]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Biology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[144,1101,1537,1689]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">
This species was collected in a hot spring, named Aguas Calientes (
<collectingRegion box="[927,1097,1537,1561]" country="Argentina" name="Jujuy" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Jujuy province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[144,263,1569,1593]" name="Argentina" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Argentina</collectingCountry>
). The temperature of the springs ranges from 46 
<superScript attach="left" box="[791,800,1565,1582]" fontSize="7" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">◦</superScript>
C to 58 
<superScript attach="left" box="[882,891,1565,1582]" fontSize="7" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">◦</superScript>
C where it emerges (
<bibRefCitation author="Miranda F &amp; Johanis P" box="[152,475,1601,1625]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222" pagination="1437 - 1441" refId="ref6058" refString="Miranda F, Johanis P. 2000 Geology and thermal features of El Ramal area, Jujuy province, Argentina. Proceedings of the World Geothermal Congress, Kyushu, Tohoku, Japan, 2000. pp: 1437 - 1441. International Geothermal Association, Aukland, New Zealand." type="proceedings paper" year="2000">Miranda and Johanis 2000</bibRefCitation>
). The larvae and metamorphotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rueda Martín &amp; Sganga, 2011" authorityName="Rueda Martín &amp; Sganga" authorityYear="2011" box="[932,1101,1601,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Smicridea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thermophila" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[932,948,1601,1625]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[969,1101,1601,1625]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">thermophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[144,231,1633,1656]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
were collected at 33 
<superScript attach="right" box="[465,474,1629,1646]" fontSize="7" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">◦</superScript>
C in a small waterfall. 
<taxonomicName box="[740,872,1632,1656]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Trichoptera</taxonomicName>
have been recorded from hot springs in North America, larvae of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hagen" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[667,905,1665,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Helicopsychidae" genus="Helicopsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borealis">
<emphasis box="[667,905,1665,1689]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2222">Helicopsyche borealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected in
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[213,1169,162,222]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2223">
Yellowstone National Park, 
<collectingRegion box="[532,640,166,190]" country="United States of America" name="Wyoming" pageId="10" pageNumber="2223">Wyoming</collectingRegion>
at 34 
<superScript attach="left" box="[702,711,162,179]" fontSize="7" pageId="10" pageNumber="2223">◦</superScript>
C (
<bibRefCitation author="Wiggins GB" box="[746,904,166,190]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2223" refId="ref6259" refString="Wiggins GB. 1996. Larvae of the North American Caddisfly Genera (Trichoptera), 2 nd edition. Toronto: University of Toronto Press." type="book" year="1996">Wiggins 1996</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first record of larvae of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curtis" authorityYear="1835" box="[349,533,198,222]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="2223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hydropsychidae</taxonomicName>
from a hot mesothermal spring.
</paragraph>
